    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-23T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 23, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 23—6:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>561. Department’s 310, November 22, 2 p.m.<note n="45" xml:id="d779fn45">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>As reported by Associated Press and other American correspondents,
                        Imperial Headquarters was established on November 20th. Its organization and
                        functions follow lines indicated in our 533.<note n="46" xml:id="d779fn46"
                            >November 12, noon, <ref target="#pg_675">p. 675</ref>.</note> A
                        statement issued that day by Imperial Headquarters is to the following
                        effect. <list>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Imperial Headquarters is an instrument by which the Emperor will
                                exercise supreme command over the army and navy. Its establishment
                                effects no change in the division between the functions and
                                responsibilities hitherto assigned respectively to the High Command
                                and to the Government and rumors to the effect that these two
                                agencies will be combined are without foundation.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                            <item>The duties of Imperial Headquarters are to advise the Emperor on
                                the exercise of supreme command, to formulate high strategical plans
                                and to assure coordination between the army and navy.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Members of the Cabinet are not to be assigned to Imperial
                                Headquarters but they will be invited to confer with Imperial
                                Headquarters when occasion arises.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Our estimate with regard to possibilities of a declaration of war as set
                        forth in paragraph 5 of our 524, November 6, 6 p.m., is still <pb
                            facs="0720" n="713" xml:id="pg_713"/> that the determining factor will
                        be whether supplies of arms and munitions to China continue in substantial
                        quantities.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
